    "client_msg_id": "8ee4d4af-9fc7-4907-b8e7-95ce1d2c473f",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Rails migrations for data, I like\n\nWould be interested to know why the term \"lens\" is more helpful than just a vanilla \"transformation\" or \"migration\"\n\n&gt; A _lens_ is a bidirectional transformation between a pair of connected data structures, capable of translating an edit on one structure into an appropriate edit on the other.\nMaybe it's so momentous that a strict new term is the only thing that suffices\n\nThat aside, looks like great work",
