            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "I've been transforming json structures like this whilst integrating and syncing data between two of my products and face the all the issues you mention in \"Augmenting Data\"\n\nI've found, as you mentioned, it's necessary to be able to lookup data, either via objects within the same payload, or making another request, in order to apply the transformation. And to be able to reverse the transformation, it's necessary to have stored information (mostly object ids) from the initial transformation.\n\nAlso, with each transfer I've found it necessary to augment the data with some assumed information on each transformation, and I'm not sure it's possible to reverse without some dataloss. I'm also not sure I can reverse the changes with a single \"lens\" as some transformations aren't reversible.\n\nNot sure if that's useful, but regardless of whether it's possible to do with or without dataloss, I think this research is great and will be a big step forward to in integrating services. I look forward to seeing where this goes!"
              }
